<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-28-0391 </DOCNO><TEXT>This is a means of absorption for the dry removal of sulfur dioxide andother harmful substances from the stack gases from boilers. The meansof absorption consists mainly of a fine-grained inorganic alkaline earthcompound, particularly a calcium and/or a magnesium compound and an additivein the form of one or more carbonic acids and/or of their alkali salts,ammonium salts or alkaline earth salts.</TEXT></DOC>